The paper deals with the acquisition of Channel State Information (CSI) in a communication system, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The system considered is a cell-free massive MIMO system, which involves a large number of distributed Access Points (APs) and a Central processing Unit (CPU), making it relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also addresses the issue of spatial correlation in the CSI acquisition process, which is a topic that falls under the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. The use of detection algorithms such as minimum mean square error (MMSE) or zero forcing (ZF) also makes it relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a quantization strategy for the CSI acquisition process, which involves the use of statistical methods, making it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
